sentences: Nathan Williams (born March 24, 1963) is an American Zydeco accordionist and singer.
In 1988 Williams performed for the first time at the New Orleans Jazz & Heritage Festival, after which he got his lucky break.
Times were hard for the Williams family and Williams lost his father when he was only seven years old.
Just five years after graduating from high school, Williams was recording 45s on his brother's El Sid independent record label.
Later he formed his band, Nathan Williams and the Zydeco Cha-Chas, with which he plays to this day.
